# Environment Configuration Example

## Required Secrets (set via wrangler secret put)

# GitHub OAuth Application Credentials
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_client_id
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_client_secret

# GitHub Webhook Secret (for webhook signature verification)
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret

# Optional: Session secret for additional security
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
SESSION_SECRET=your_session_secret

## Setting Secrets

Use the Wrangler CLI to set secrets:

```bash
wrangler secret put GITHUB_CLIENT_ID
wrangler secret put GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET
wrangler secret put GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET
wrangler secret put SESSION_SECRET
```

## Environment Variables (set in wrangler.toml)

# Your worker's callback URL
GITHUB_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-worker.workers.dev/auth/callback
